data.name: 0000 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: So that's what we went with. I decided to take Nagato with me to the computer lab--

data.name: 0001 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hey, Nagato. Can I ask you something?

data.name: 0002 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: What?

data.name: 0003 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: A moment ago, you know how we just entered class 1-10?

data.name: 0004 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Did you see what happened before that? A silhouette was floating outside the window…

data.name: 0006 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: My bad, I realize I'm saying something strange. At any rate, it was on the 2nd floor.

data.name: 0007 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I originially thought I was just seeing things, but there was also that classroom.

data.name: 0008 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If Haruhi said "I wish for that!" even a ghost parade could show itself in reality.

data.name: 0009 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Was that also Haruhi's doing?

data.name: 0011 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Are you listening, Nagato?

data.name: 0012 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I'm listening.

data.name: 0013 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If that's the case, why don't you give me a reply or two?

data.name: 0014 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Relatedly, whether the computer society lot will give us any info is causing me limitless anxiety.

data.name: 0015 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If you're wondering if Nagato is well suited to witness investigation, the answer is NO.

data.name: 0016 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: … I'll just end up suffering, after all. That's what always happens…

data.name: 0017 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Since I joined the Haruhi faction, I feel as though I've grown mentally.

data.name: 0018 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: … Although I'm not entirely happy about that…

data.name: 0019 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Which reminds me, Nagato, have you been getting value out of that PC in the clubroom?

data.name: 0021 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato silently gave a slight tilt of the head.

data.name: 0022 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I just felt like the so-called "personal computer" would be a good fit for Nagato.

data.name: 0023 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: You see, there's lots of things it can be used for.

data.name: 0024 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: For example, you can search through the library's collection of books or something.

data.name: 0025 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: No need.

data.name: 0026 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I know of all of the books in the library.

data.name: 0027 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: …Then, If I were to ask you if they had a specific book, could you answer?

data.name: 0028 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Possibly.

data.name: 0029 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: In that case, it's pointless to look it up on a PC, huh…

data.name: 0030 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Don't tell me this person has already read through the library's entire catalog...?

data.name: 0031 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: No, it's nothing, forget about it.

data.name: 0032 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I see.

data.name: 0033 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Come to think of it, Nagato might have something even more impressive than a PC.

data.name: 0034 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: However if that's the case, our PC is nothing more than waste of space isn't it.

data.name: 0036 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I know it's stating the obvious, but the clubroom was covered in PCs.

data.name: 0037 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The thought arises every time I come here, but this place reeks of brand-new electronics.

data.name: 0038 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It gave off a similar impression to the electronics section at a mass retailer.

data.name: 0039 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Then, the computer club members…

data.name: 0040 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: They were each facing their computer monitors, fully absorbed in striking their keyboards.

data.name: 0041 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It seems like they're in the middle of something important, so I'll wait for the right timing to make our presence known.

data.name: 0042 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: When I think about it, It's impressive that they can get so many people together for club activities in the summer holiday.

data.name: 0043 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: However, I'm in no position to comment on other people's business.

data.name: 0044 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Much to my dismay, the SOS Brigade is also in the middle of its infamous club activities.

data.name: 0046 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'm guessing that Nagato's silence isn't because she's calculating the right timing.

data.name: 0047 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Looks like I'll have to make the first move after all.

data.name: 0049 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Huh? You guys are back again? What the hell is it this time!?

data.name: 0050 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Thankfully, the other party called out to me first.

data.name: 0051 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: As you can see, We're busy! If you've come to disturb us, get out!

data.name: 0052 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I didn't expect a warm welcome, but I didn't anticipate such a cold-hearted one either.

data.name: 0053 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: We're not exactly here to disturb you. We were wondering if we could hear the story from before in more detail…

data.name: 0054 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Story from before? Ahh… that ghost story, huh?

data.name: 0055 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: … We already told your club president, right?

data.name: 0056 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: If you mean Haruhi, she's off doing something on her own.

data.name: 0057 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'd like to add that he can therefore relax, but that would be awkward. I'll just keep that one to myself.

data.name: 0058 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: I see… In that case, it's fine.

data.name: 0059 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Actually, no, it's not fine. I really am busy right now.

data.name: 0060 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It only needs to take a second.

data.name: 0061 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: You could just say it was a mere misjudgement, or misunderstanding, or something.

data.name: 0062 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I just want to go over the eyewitness testimonies again.

data.name: 0063 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Wow… You guys sure have it rough, having to work under her. Sounds troublesome.

data.name: 0064 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Of all things, he started sympathizing with me.

data.name: 0065 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It's only occasional, but there are definitely times when I wished someone would understand us.

data.name: 0066 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: And yet, now that it's actually happened, why does it feel so uncomfortable?

data.name: 0067 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: And you there... You were in the literature club, weren't you? Poor thing.

data.name: 0069 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Come to think of it, Nagato was in the literature club, and our clubroom was theirs.

data.name: 0070 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: To be honest, it should've stayed that way… Probably.

data.name: 0071 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, you're still technically in the literature club, aren't you?

data.name: 0072 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I still am.

data.name: 0073 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: The clubroom too, is also more or less still the literature club's… even now.

data.name: 0074 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Yes.

data.name: 0075 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: In other words, you've completly rented out the room, Haruhi.

data.name: 0076 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Actually, it benefits no-one to call it "renting."

data.name: 0077 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: "Give an inch, and they'll take a mile" is a more appropriate term for this situation.

data.name: 0078 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi has the nerve to just take the whole mile from the very start.

data.name: 0079 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Right now, Nagato is a member of the SOS Brigade, and that's good enough for me.

data.name: 0080 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Though, the literature club, huh… if I'm not mistaken, Nagato was the only member.

data.name: 0081 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I haven't seen anything in the clubroom that suggests they assigned any club activities.

data.name: 0082 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'm amazed the club hasn't been shut down.

data.name: 0083 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: I sympathize with your situation, but how many times do I have to tell you that we're--

data.name: 0085 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: B-big trouble! Presideeent!

data.name: 0086 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: The server is… Our data hangar is...!

data.name: 0087 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Wh-what is it!? What's going on?

data.name: 0088 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: We've got big trouble! It won't boot up anymore! It's not responding!

data.name: 0089 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: What…!? Reboot it again!

data.name: 0091 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: No matter how many times I try it doesn't seem to work… It might be physically damaged…

data.name: 0092 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: What about the backups!? All the data was copied, as it should've been, right!?

data.name: 0094 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: That's… Not yet… I was just about to, but it completely stopped working…

data.name: 0095 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I thought it had gotten noisy, and sure enough, some big trouble seemed to have broken out.

data.name: 0096 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Unbelievable… To think you were just about to…

data.name: 0097 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The president groaned with an expression of dispair closely resembling Munch's masterpiece, "The Scream."

data.name: 0098 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Looks like there's something wrong with your computer…

data.name: 0099 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: All our hard work… Our entire summer of toil is completely wasted…

data.name: 0100 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: Ohh, even though we made this much…

data.name: 0101 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: President, everyone… I'm sorry. If only I had backed it up sooner…

data.name: 0103 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The air was heavy like a funeral wake. It didn't look like we'd be able to hear the story now.

data.name: 0104 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Wait, hold on...?

data.name: 0105 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Maybe I can use this situation to get them to lower their guard a little.

data.name: 0106 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, can't you do something about this?

data.name: 0107 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Do what?

data.name: 0108 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It seems like these guys have a problem. What's happening here--can you fix it?

data.name: 0110 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato stared blankly at the broken computer before eventually--

data.name: 0111 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It is possible.

data.name: 0112 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: … Would you mind doing it, then? I'm not trying to earn their favor or anything, but…

data.name: 0113 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It might put them in a bit of a better mood.

data.name: 0114 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Understood.

data.name: 0117 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Ah-- Mr. President. The truth is, Nagato here is very knowledgeable about computers.

data.name: 0118 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: She might be able to fix it.

data.name: 0119 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: You really mean it!? You can really fix it!?

data.name: 0120 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, please fix it.

data.name: 0121 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Commencing repairs.

data.name: 0122 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato stood in front of the broken PC… And suddenly plugged it into the wall outlet.

data.name: 0123 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Wha…!?

data.name: 0124 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Finished.

data.name: 0125 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: Wha!? P-P-P-President!

data.name: 0126 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: What is it this time…? What else could possibly have gone wrong…?

data.name: 0128 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: I-It booted up! The server suddenly restarted…!

data.name: 0129 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: R-Really!? How's the data!?

data.name: 0130 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: Give me a second… It's okay, it's all still there!

data.name: 0131 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It is recommended to make a backup immediately.

data.name: 0132 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Make a backup right away! And then, run a virus scan too!

data.name: 0133 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Ahh, thank goodness… For a moment there I didn't know what was going to happen…

data.name: 0134 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The president was trembling with emotion as if to say, "Thank you, God!"

data.name: 0135 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It seems your machine troubles blew over without a hitch. Very good, very good.

data.name: 0136 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Ahh… You two just witnessed something outrageous. I'm sure it was surprising.

data.name: 0137 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: My heart nearly stopped-- Anyways, I'm relieved. Good grief.

data.name: 0138 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: But how exactly were you able to fix it?

data.name: 0139 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: It seemed like you repaired it in no time.

data.name: 0140 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I don't need to honestly inform him that it was just unplugged from the outlet do I.

data.name: 0141 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'll do what I can here to preserve his sense of gratitude.

data.name: 0142 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Well, It seems like that was very important data.

data.name: 0143 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Are you making a program or something?

data.name: 0144 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: …So, I asked something unrelated.

data.name: 0145 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Oh? Are you interested?

data.name: 0146 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: It's just as you say! We're working on some- thing that will make Computer Society history.

data.name: 0147 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Well you see, we're making what you would refer to as a "game program."

data.name: 0148 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Well, it's really just extremely back-breaking work. It's an immense task.

data.name: 0149 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: What happened to their wariness towards us…? The president seems to be in a good mood.

data.name: 0150 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: We even had quite an argument over choosing a programming language.

data.name: 0151 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Though, I'm glad we decided to go object-oriented, because of those specs.

data.name: 0153 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: See, there's only so much you're able to do with a standard library right?

data.name: 0154 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: On top of that, the GUI was a huge issue, and the screen design problem too--

data.name: 0155 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Jargon started flying out all over the place. I don't understand any of this at all.

data.name: 0157 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: But unlike me, Nagato was listening quietly. I wonder if she understands it?

data.name: 0158 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: In addition, we've finished writing most of the source code.

data.name: 0159 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Well, that was a fascinating conver- sation. As expected of the experts-only computer club.

data.name: 0160 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Y-You think so? I wouldn't take it that far. Ahahaha…

data.name: 0161 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: On the dawn of it's completion, you guys'--

data.name: 0162 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: … Ah, that's right.

data.name: 0163 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Suddenly, the president covered his mouth. What is it, all of a sudden?

data.name: 0164 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: … Weren't you two also members of that SOS group, now that I think about it?

data.name: 0165 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Unfortunately, I cant deny that.

data.name: 0166 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Never mind, forget about it.

data.name: 0167 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: From the beginning, this was a topic that I couldn't follow at all, so I won't push my luck.

data.name: 0168 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: ……Information collecting.

data.name: 0169 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: That's right, we want to hear the story concerning the classroom from before.

data.name: 0170 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Ah, Class 1-10 ghost stories and the like. I think we already said everything last time.

data.name: 0171 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Is there anything you forgot……Even something like a small detail?

data.name: 0172 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Hey, did you forget to say anything about the Class 1-10 thing?

data.name: 0173 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The president called out to club member A who was working in front of the server.

data.name: 0174 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: Yeah……

data.name: 0175 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: My bad, but I cant remember. I do feel like there was something though.

data.name: 0176 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_A (部員Ａ)
data.value: But, what's so important about it?

data.name: 0177 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: A global crisis is happening, or that's what I'd like to say at least……

data.name: 0179 (365.ja) CLUB_MEM_B (部員Ｂ)
data.value: The back up and virus scan are complete～

data.name: 0180 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: Alright, we're back in business.

data.name: 0181 (365.ja) CLUB_PRES (部長氏)
data.value: You guys……I'm sorry but, any time now……

data.name: 0182 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: This is it, it doesn't look I'll be able to get anything more out of them before times up……

data.name: 0183 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I'm sorry for bothering you.

data.name: 0184 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, let's pull out now.

data.name: 0186 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I might have been imagining it, but for just a moment Nagato's face seemed disappointed.

data.name: 0187 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Nagato… Did she want to stay here a bit longer and keep listening? That couldn't be it.

data.name: 0188 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, do you want to stay and talk a bit more?

data.name: 0189 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Why?

data.name: 0190 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Well……No reason in particular.

data.name: 0191 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I thought maybe, you might want to talk to the president or look at the club equipment more.

data.name: 0192 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Just a little.

data.name: 0193 (365.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: But, it is fine.

data.name: 0194 (365.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Is it……? In that case, alright then.

data.name: 0195 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I wonder how the computer club's equipment and program look to Nagato's eyes.

data.name: 0196 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Either way, I didn't expect listening to them talk would end up becoming such a clamor.

data.name: 0197 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: The summer training camp has only just begun, so who knows what the future holds……

data.name: 0198 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It the end, it seems I couldn't get any new info at all. Good grief……

data.name: 0199 (365.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Well then, I wonder what I should do from here.

data.name: 0200 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Talk to them a bit more.

data.name: 0201 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Don't talk to them any more.

data.name: 0202 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Get confirmation from Nagato.

data.name: 0203 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Don't ask for details.

data.name: 0204 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Do you want to stay a bit longer?

data.name: 0205 (365.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: It's probably just my imagination.
